{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Karia ARIA Backend",
    "description": "Colección del servicio Express **aria-backend**.\n\n- **Raíz:** `GET /health` (liveness, sin prefijo).\n- **API:** prefijo `{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/` (por defecto `karia-svc/v2`).\n\n**Contrato detallado (solo PostgreSQL):** `docs/API_DATABASE_ENDPOINTS.md` en el repo.\n\nAjusta **baseUrl** (ej. `http://localhost:3000`). Los bodies usan **camelCase** como en la API.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "apiPrefix", "value": "karia-svc/v2" },
    { "key": "initiativeId", "value": "init-uuid-ejemplo" },
    { "key": "artifactDefId", "value": "def-uuid-ejemplo" },
    { "key": "libraryFileId", "value": "lib-1234567890-nombre-archivo.txt" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Raíz (probes)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Liveness (raíz)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
            "description": "Respuesta plano: `OK`. No usa el prefijo `/karia-svc/v2`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Liveness (API)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/health",
            "description": "Controlador de salud bajo el prefijo de ingress. Respuesta plano: `healthy`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Health DB",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/health/db",
            "description": "Prueba `SELECT 1` contra Postgres. Siempre **HTTP 200** con JSON:\n- éxito: `{ \"success\": true }`\n- fallo: `{ \"success\": false, \"error\": \"...\" }` (sin `ConnectionString_Karia`, error de red, SSL, etc.).\nSin query ni body."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Initiatives",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List initiatives",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/initiatives",
            "description": "`SELECT * FROM initiative ORDER BY created_at DESC`. Respuesta: **array** de objetos (camelCase). No incluye `createdAt`/`updatedAt` en el JSON de salida."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create initiative",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"id\": \"{{initiativeId}}\",\n  \"name\": \"Mi iniciativa\",\n  \"type\": \"Run\",\n  \"product\": null,\n  \"startDate\": null,\n  \"endDate\": null,\n  \"quarter\": null,\n  \"status\": null,\n  \"intakeRequestId\": null,\n  \"currentGateId\": \"G0\",\n  \"pipelineActivated\": false,\n  \"artifacts\": []\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/initiatives",
            "description": "Servicio valida **id** y **name** (400 si faltan). En `schemaV2.sql`, **`type` es nullable**; si se omite queda NULL. Valores distintos de **Run** / **Change** violan el CHECK y suelen devolver 500.\nRecomendación: enviar siempre `type` Run|Change. Opcionales: `product`, `currentGateId` (default G0 en código), fechas, `quarter`, `status`, `intakeRequestId`, `pipelineActivated` (default false), `artifacts` (array, default []).\n200: objeto Initiative creado."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update initiative",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Nombre actualizado\",\n  \"status\": \"active\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/initiatives/{{initiativeId}}",
            "description": "PATCH semántico: solo se actualizan claves presentes. Válidas: `name`, `product`, `currentGateId`, `type`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `quarter`, `status`, `intakeRequestId`, `pipelineActivated`, `artifacts`. El `id` del body no cambia la fila (usa el de la URL).\n404 si no existe; 400 si el objeto está vacío."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete initiative",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/initiatives/{{initiativeId}}",
            "description": "Sin body. Respuesta 200 siempre `{ \"success\": true }` (incluso si el id no existía — DELETE idempotente en el código actual)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Intakes (solo lectura)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List intakes",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/intakes",
            "description": "Solo **GET**. `SELECT * FROM intake_request ORDER BY created_at DESC`. Array de intakes (camelCase); `createdAt` es solo fecha **YYYY-MM-DD**. No hay POST/PUT/DELETE en Express."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Artifact definitions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List artifact definitions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifact-definitions",
            "description": "`ORDER BY gate, name`. Array con `id`, `gate`, `name`, `initiativeType`, `predecessorIds`, `description`, `mandatory`, `area`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt` (ISO)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create artifact definition",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"id\": \"{{artifactDefId}}\",\n  \"gate\": \"G1\",\n  \"name\": \"Documento de visión\",\n  \"description\": \"Opcional\",\n  \"initiativeType\": \"Both\",\n  \"predecessorIds\": [],\n  \"mandatory\": false,\n  \"area\": \"Producto\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifact-definitions",
            "description": "400 sin **id**, **gate** o **name**.\nOpcionales: `initiativeType` (default Both), `predecessorIds` (array, default []), `description`, `mandatory` (default false), `area` (default Producto).\n200: objeto creado con `createdAt`/`updatedAt`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update artifact definition",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"description\": \"Texto actualizado\",\n  \"mandatory\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifact-definitions/{{artifactDefId}}",
            "description": "Campos actualizables si van en el JSON: `gate`, `name`, `initiativeType`, `description`, `mandatory`, `area`, `predecessorIds` (array → JSON en BD). 404 si no existe; 400 sin campos."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete artifact definition",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifact-definitions/{{artifactDefId}}",
            "description": "200 `{ \"success\": true }` siempre (misma idempotencia que DELETE initiative)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Library (GCS)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List library files",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/library/files",
            "description": "Requiere credenciales GCP (ADC / `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Signed upload URL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"filename\": \"mi-contexto.md\",\n  \"category\": \"Contexto\",\n  \"contentType\": \"text/markdown\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/library/upload-url",
            "description": "`category` debe ser una de: **Contexto**, **Output**, **Prompt**, **Template**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Signed download URL",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/library/download/{{libraryFileId}}",
            "description": "`fileId` es el id devuelto al crear upload (p. ej. `lib-...`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete library file",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/library/delete/{{libraryFileId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Artifacts / Output (GCS)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List artifact output files",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifacts/files"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Publish artifact (Markdown)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"initiativeName\": \"Mi iniciativa\",\n  \"artifactName\": \"Informe\",\n  \"gate\": \"G1\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"content\": \"# Título\\n\\nCuerpo en Markdown.\",\n  \"contentType\": \"text/markdown\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifacts/publish",
            "description": "**artifactName** y **content** son los campos clave. `initiativeId` o `initiativeName` según negocio."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Publish artifact (PDF)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/pdf" },
              { "key": "initiativename", "value": "Mi iniciativa", "description": "Cabecera en minúsculas (Express)." },
              { "key": "artifactname", "value": "Informe" },
              { "key": "gate", "value": "G1" },
              { "key": "version", "value": "1.0" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "text" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/{{apiPrefix}}/artifacts/publish-pdf",
            "description": "Body **binario** PDF (`application/pdf`, límite 50 MB). En Postman: pestaña Body → **binary** y elige un `.pdf`. Las cabeceras `initiativename`, `artifactname`, `gate`, `version` son opcionales pero típicas."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
